# Fishing Area Fishing is available on the shores near either a fish sign or where a fish icon is displayed on the mini-map. - The map you fish on and the bait you use will affect your catch. * Fishing will only be available in the event field as of the July 17, 2019 (Wed) maintenance (JST/UTC +9). - You must complete the Main Quest "The Indomitable Fang" to take part in this event. - You can travel to the special map via the NPC Nishida. We plan to add further features and fishing areas in future updates. We hope you're looking forward to them!
# Fishing Preparation When players enter a fishing area, the normal attack button in the lower right of the screen will become a start fishing button. Tapping the start fishing button will take you to the fishing preparation screen. Tap the icons in the upper left of the screen to equip a fishing rod and bait. You can purchase fishing rods and bait from the Merchant. You can also make fishing rods at the workshop if you have the right production materials. You can trade for fishing rod production materials at the Fish Trader. - Players start with the "Fishing Rod borrowed from Nishida" equipped. „ÄÄPlayers can use the Fishing Rod borrowed from Nishida up until they equip a new fishing rod. - Using different types and rarities of baits will make certain fish easier or harder to catch. After you've equipped a fishing rod and bait, tap the cast button in the lower right of the screen to start fishing.
# How to Fish + When the fish bites your bait, a blue exclamation mark and hook gauge will appear. Tap the hook button in the lower right of the screen while the hook gauge is visible to hook the fish. The orange exclamation marks that display when you hook the fish indicate the fish's rarity. More exclamation marks indicate a higher rarity. After hooking the fish, a timing gauge, HP gauge, hook icons (hook points), and Escape will appear. Timing Gauge There are three timing categories: Perfect (Lime Green), Good (Pale Green), and Miss (Purple). * Perfect: Greatly decreases the fish's HP. * Good: Decreases the fish's HP, but also increases Escape. * Miss: Increases Escape. * Time-Out: After the timing gauge increases and decreases 3 times, it will time out and the fish's Escape will increase. + HP Gauge Tapping the timing button in the bottom right of the screen with good timing will decrease the fish's HP. Once it reaches 0, you can catch the fish. + Escape The higher the Escape, the higher the chance your hook points will decrease. + Hook Points The fish will escape once you have lost all three hook points. * You can lose hook points even with Perfect timing, depending on how high Escape is.
# Your Catch When you successfully catch a fish, you will also earn FExp (Fishing Experience). You can trade the fish you've caught for fishing rod production materials and other items at the Trader. Gaining FExp will raise your fishing level. Check the Status screen for more details, accessible from the preparation screen that displays after you tap the start fishing button in fishing areas. # Fishing Rods Raising your fishing level will allow you to equip different rods that match your level. * You are able to produce or purchase any rod, even if you aren't leveled enough to equip them. Tap the fish icon in the Merchant screen to view the purchasable rods. Tap the item icon in the workshop to view rods that can be produced. * For more details on the stats and required levels of individual rods, tap and hold each fishing rod icon on the fishing preparation screen (viewable after you select start fishing in a fishing area). * To check individual stats, tap the start fishing button and select Status from the preparation screen in a fishing area.

Players managing to get a score higher than 1629 Points during the time period can get 250 Arcana Gems! Boss weakness is slash https://discordapp.com/channels/386622427393949705/406655326679728128/411123950731657216
Credits to official server as always @Don‚Äôt Panic Member @deleted-role
Monsters, weapons and skills have an attribute. These attributes are: Slash (red) Hit (yellow) Rush (green) They have a rock-paper-scissor like connection, if you hit a monster with a weapon/skill that has an advantageous attribute on the top right of the screen a ‚ÄúWeakness‚Äù appears and the attack does more damage. https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/386626653486579714/391074516916502529/image.jpg
Aside from normal attributes sword skills also have natural attributes, the effectiveness of natural attributes depend on the attacked monster. https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/386626653486579714/391076015381807114/image.png
From up to bottom: Fire Water Wind Earth Light Darkness The attribute of a sword skill can be seen on the icon next to the normal attribute icon. Credits @djh37564

Notice for those users logging on to "Sword Art Online Integral Factor." Fishing rod effects are being increased overall to make it easier to distinguish between each type's strengths and weaknesses. ÔΩ∞Planned Adjustment Date During the August 7, 2019 (Wed) maintenance. ÔΩ∞Planned Adjustments Details Fishing Rod Status Adjustments Adjusted to have the fish's strength deplete with "Good" timing based on the Power and Control values. Adjusted to have the fish's strength greatly deplete with "Perfect" timing based on Technic values. For this round of adjustments, we have clarified and strengthened the differences between rod types. ÔΩ∞Control, High Control, and Royal Control Rods The timing gauge slows down to make getting a "Perfect" easier. These fishing rods are perfect for catching fish with fast timing gauges. ÔΩ∞Technical, High Technical, and Royal Technical Rods Although the timing gauge speeds up, these rods decrease the fish's strength the most with "Perfect" timing. These fishing rods give you an advantage against fish with lots of strength when you have "Perfect" timing. ÔΩ∞Powerful, High Powerful, and Royal Powerful Rods Both "Perfect" and "Good" timings will reduce a moderate amount of the fish's strength. These fishing rods are easy to use and have no special quirks. Adjusted fishing rod parameters as follows. To ensure everyone enjoys the fishing feature, more adjustments may be made. * The quest schedule may be subject to change without notice. Thank you for your understanding.

# Fishing Ranking [8/21 15:00 (JST/UTC+9) UPDATE] Ranking Rewards have been distributed. Please collect them from the present box. For more details about the rewards, see "Ranking Rewards" below.
Yuuki Incense Event === Following the maintenance on August 21, 2019 (Wed), the Stand-off with Master Yuuki will begin. # Event Period Starts after the August 21, 2019 Maintenance and ends before the August 28, 2019 Maintenance(JST/UTC+9) * The quest schedule may be subject to change without notice. Thank you for your understanding. # Effects Incense to increase Exp and Incense to increase Luck effects will activate once a monster is defeated. * EXP gained during quests will not be boosted. If you use Guild Skills with the same effect at the same time, the effect rates will be added together. Example: Only Incense to increase Exp „ÄÄ/* EXP earned: 100% increase (2x increase) * Incense to increase Exp + Guild Skill (Player EXP UP I) „ÄÄ/* EXP earned: 100% + 10% = 110% increase (2.1x increase) * # Item Expiration /* There is an expiration date on the Incense to increase Exp and Incense to increase Luck. * /* The items will disappear once the time limit has passed. * Incense to increase Exp - Until 2019/08/29 3:59 (JST/UTC+9) Incense to increase Luck - Until 2019/08/29 3:59 (JST/UTC+9)
About Changes to Incense to increase Exp and Incense to increase Luck „ÉªChanged item expiration. Changed the items, Incense to increase Exp and Incense to increase Luck, from the ongoing event so they expire uniformly. „ÉªChanged treatment of items overlapping effects. When using multiple items with the same effects, their expiration time will now increase instead of the effect's potency.

1

Thank you for your understanding. - Event details Teleport Gate Plaza - Event details In this Raising Assisting Character Dungeon, players can earn more EXP than usual. Additionally, players can acquire stamina restoration items and gift items through Score and Challenge Rewards. This Raising Assisting Character Dungeon can be cleared once per day. * This Raising Assisting Character Dungeon is updated daily at 4:00 am (JST/UTC+9). Permanent Fishing on 22F ------------------------------- The 22F fishing maps, Serene Shore and Peaceful Forest Path (day and night versions), are now permanently available as of the maintenance on August 28, 2019 (Wed). Talk to NPC Nishida in the Teleport Gate Plaza to go to 22F. 3 Traders and new items to fish for are here to go with the permanent fishing on 22F! Avatar Trader Get Moon Stone at the Fishing Trader and exchange for Kirito's and Asuna's Avatar Costumes! There are also other Avatars like straw hats available! Tradable Item List Amount Needed Trade Limit Black Sweatshirt 40 1 Black Sweatpants 20 1 Yellow Sweater 40 2 Brown Skirt 20 2 Straw Fishing Hat 20 2 Fish Basket 20 2 -Avatars (Check in-game news) -Rusted Weapon Trader Get Star Stone at the Fishing Trader and exchange for items necessary to produce the new Succession item Lost Epic Equipment. * The value and type of the bonus are random. * Integral Series cannot be used in Succession. * You can fish for Rusted Weapon or get it at the Trader. Trade "Rusted Weapon Trader" for special items. Tradable Item List Amount Needed Trade Limit Rusted Sword 40 1 Rusted Rapier 40 1 Rusted Mace 40 1 Rusted Lance 40 1 Rusted Axe 40 1 Rusted Shield 40 1 Rusted Dagger 40 1 Rusted Bow 40 1 Rusted Armor 40 1 Rusted Greaves 40 1 * The Rusted Weapon Trader trade limit will reset on the 1st of every month at 4:00 (JST/UTC+9). -Fishing Trader Trade the rare fishing item Arcana Gem Trade Ticket for Arcana Gems. Trade the fish you catch for Moon Stone or Star Stone, which can be used at the Avatar Trader and the Rusted Weapon Trader respectively. You can also trade for other items like Medal of Combat Arts, Core Metals, or fishing rod production materials. * The Fishing Trader trade limit will reset on the 1st of every month at 4:00 (JST/UTC+9). Check the Trader in-game for details!

#Issues with currently available "Grand Order" "Notice for those users logging on to "Sword Art Online Integral Factor." We have confirmed an issue with the currently available "Grand Order", where the Step function was not working correctly for some users. We have confirmed that the issue described above has been fixed and the Step function is currently working correctly. For customers who experienced the issue where the Step function of the "Grand Order" was not working correctly, we will be returning the amount of Arcana Gems used in the "Grand Order". Concerned Players - Players who experienced the issue where the Step function of the "Grand Order" was not working correctly. Return Items - The amount of Arcana Gems used when the "Grand Order" was not working correctly. *Please claim within 30 days. We apologize for the inconvenience caused at this time.
#Regarding iOS 13 Update Thank you very much for playing SWORD ART ONLINE: Integral Factor. We expect that Apple Inc. will release the new iOS 13 soon. There is a possibility that parts of the game will not function normally right after the new update. We ask that players use caution when updating. We recommend doing the following as a safeguard for potential game data loss or other issues. Create a Data Transfer ID & Password On your current device, tap the "Menu" button in the upper-left corner of the title screen. Then, tap the "Create Transfer ID" button. After tapping the "Create Transfer ID" button, you'll be taken to the Transfer ID creation page, where your Transfer ID will be generated. You will also be asked to set a password for the transfer process. Once you've completed these steps, be sure to record both your generated Transfer ID and password and save it for later. Many players have lost screenshots of this information as a result of lost or broken phones. We recommend recording your Transfer ID and password somewhere aside from your smartphone. As always, thank you for playing. We hope that you continue to enjoy Sword Art Online: Integral Factor.

Users stated that the activation requirements for the Burst feature were difficult and unintuitive to use. Sword Art Online: Integral Factor #global-server-news BOT 13-Nov-19 03:49 AM
PSA: if the skill numbers on Yui bot seems too good to be true, it probably is. I‚Äôve recently received numerous reports of the Yui bot displaying flat constant buffs as percentages instead, leading to absurd buffs like 40%/50% attack. Here‚Äôs a notice that says, yeah, you guys are right. It isn‚Äôt that good, and it‚Äôs supposed to be flat instead of %. How did it happen? The game database stores all the numbers in weird ways, and sometimes buff constants and percentages are stored in identical ways, with the only difference being the magnitude of the number, so I need to find a way to decide if it should‚Äôve been a % or not. Apparently, there‚Äôs some really bad coding here (oopsie) that mis-assign % to flat buffs for some skills, resulting in an OP skill (if true, but it‚Äôs not). How can I fix it? Thing is... I can‚Äôt do anything now, or more like, I don‚Äôt have time to fix the bug, simply because the entire code for this is hacky cause it was supposedly a PoC, so I‚Äôll be planning to rewrite the entire portion of the code for this, which I won‚Äôt have the time to, until after 29th November. Conclusion Please do use the bot to check for the numbers and information, but if the buff numbers in % seems too godly, maybe it‚Äôs actually a mistake and is supposed to be flat. I‚Äôm really sorry about this! Summary The actual words and everything are accurate, except for the numbers and %, which may be in-accurate in that % may actually be flat. Please take caution. Should anyone have any questions, feel free to DM me at my discord handle, and I‚Äôll try my best to answer your queries! Yui‚Äôs developer, Nayuta Kani#0002 (edited)

-Boost Mode is a monthly subscription that gives you the following boosts: -Boost Content Boost 1: Get 4x EXP when hunting monsters. Boost 2: Get 2x Weapon Proficiency when hunting monsters. Boost 3: 2x item drop rate when hunting monsters. *If you use items with the same effect at the same time with the Boost Mode, the effects will be calculated as follows: [In the case where the default state of earning EXP is set as 30] 1) Boost Mode will 4 times earning the EXP (+90); 2) An additional item is used to double earning EXP on top of it (+30); Then, 30 (default state) + 90 (from above #1) + 30 (from above #2) = 150, which makes the earning of EXP increased by 5 times. -Important „ÉªBoost Mode is valid for a month starting from the purchased date and will be automatically renewed each month. „ÉªIf cancelled during the validity period, you will continue receiving effect of the boosts until you log out after the expiration date. „ÉªYou cannot make duplicate purchases during the validity period. „ÉªPlease be aware that deleting the app does not cancel this subscription. -Payment, Duration, Renewal „ÉªPayment of this subscription will be made through Apple ID. „ÉªIf cancellation is not made 24 hours prior to the expiration date, the subscription will be renewed automatically. „ÉªThe one-month subscription will be renewed automatically within 24 hours before the expiry date and monthly charges will occur at every renewal.
-Cancellation „ÉªThis subscription must be canceled at least 24 hours prior to the expiration date. „ÉªCancellation may be completed through the following procedure. 1. Tap Settings > [your name] > iTunes & App Store 2. Tap "Apple ID" at the top of the screen. 3. Tap "View Apple ID" then "Subscriptions" 4. Tap "Boost Mode" purchased on "SWORD ART ONLINE: Integral Factor" to see the purchase history. 5. Cancel subscription by tapping "Cancel Subscription" Other Precautions „ÉªThere is a possibility that connection problems may occur when purchasing, so please do not close the application while purchase is still processing. „ÉªTerms of Service https://legal.bandainamcoent.co.jp/terms „ÉªPrivacy Policy https://legal.bandainamcoent.co.jp/privacy

# Skill Record Awakening and Rush Recollection implemented!
New features Skill Record Awakening and Rush Recollection will be added to the game as of November 29. You will be able to awaken and upgrade the Awakening Level using the Awakening materials Awakening Star and Jewels. Awakening skill records will be able to use a powerful temporary boost called "Rush Recollection", granting you "Recollection Skill" that give you an advantage in combat. # ‚ñ†Rush Recollection Activating Rush Recollection will grant you baseline effects that temporarily increase your speed, max HP, and damage dealt. Equipping multiple Awakening skill records will enhance their max HP and damage boosting effects in correlation to the set's total Awakening Level. # ‚ñ†Recollection Skill Recollection Skill are bonus effects that activate at the same time as Rush Recollection and differ depending on the Skill Record you Awakening. Recollection Skill effectiveness will be bolstered with each Awakening Level. Plus, all Recollection Skill will activate when you equip multiple Awakening skill records. * Awakening skill records will activate even if their equipment type differs. * Partners and Assisting Characters can't use Rush Recollection even if they equip Awakening skill records. # ‚ñ†Counter Your Enemy's Formidable Chaos Recollection Damage-Reduction Buff You'll find this useful in fights against Boss Monsters with Chaos Recollection, a powerful buff that reduces incoming damage. Damage boosted by Rush Recollection will pierce your opponent's defenses by nullifying the Chaos Recollection damage reduction effect. Use it strategically to turn the battle in your favor.
# ‚ñ†Enhancing Rush Recollection Max HP and Damage Boosts Effectiveness increases in accordance to the number of Awakening skill records and Awakening Level. Equipping 1 Awakening skill records gives you a 20% boost, plus 2% for each Awakening Level. Enhancement Example: Equipping 1 Skill Record at Awakening Level 1 gives you a 22% boost to max HP and damage during Rush Recollection Equipping 1 Skill Record at Awakening Level 2 gives you a 24% boost to max HP and damage during Rush Recollection Equipping 2 Skill Records at Awakening Level 2 gives you a 28% boost to max HP and damage during Rush Recollection # ‚ñ†Rush Gauge The Rush gauge automatically fills up over time and recovers completely when you enter a safe area such as a town. The more the gauge fills, the longer you will be able to activate Rush Recollection. *Gauge will continue to be restored automatically even when logged out of the game. Press the "Rush" button on the right of the screen to activate Rush Recollection. # ‚ñ†How to Perform Awakening Speak to the blacksmith NPC and select a Skill Record. You can use materials from the Awakening tab on the left to perform Awakening. * The type and amount of materials required will differ depending on each Skill Record. * Awakening have a certain chance to succeed and some may produce a "Fail" result. # ‚ñ†Aura Size and Color Players will gain an Aura when Rush Recollection activates, and traces of the Aura will remain while the skill is active. The Aura will increase in size for each Awakening skill records in the same set. The color of the Aura also corresponds to the set's total Skill Record Awakening Level. # ‚ñ†Causes of Rush Recollection Effect Expiring Timing out. Player enters a near-death state. Player opens a menu. Player performs a quick change.
